## Interfaces / Contracts

No external API or SQL contract changes.

Planned internal helper to improve testability while preserving public behavior:

```go
func (s *WorkspaceService) resolveInviteMembership(
    ctx context.Context,
    db store.DB,
    workspaceID, userID string,
) (*domain.Membership, error)
```

Behavior:
- return existing membership as-is when found
- otherwise create a new viewer membership
- never downgrade an existing role

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Unit | Existing member keeps role (`admin`, `cm`, `viewer`) | Table-driven service tests around the helper using a spy `store.DB`; assert returned role and that no insert SQL is issued for existing members. |
| Unit | New member still joins as viewer | Same spy-based test; assert membership insert occurs once with `viewer`. |
| Unit | Successful existing-member claim still consumes invite use | Assert `IncrementInviteUse` path executes for both existing and new-member cases. |
| Integration | HTTP invite claim still returns `201` + membership envelope | Keep/update `TestInvite_Claim_ReturnsMembership`; this protects handler contract, not the downgrade rule. |

